title: [Columbian Exposition and World's Fair collection]
scope_and_con_note_1: Dummy for The historical World's Columbian Exposition and Chicago guide ... / by Horace H. Morgan. St. Louis, Mo. : Pacific Pub. Co., 1892 (salesman's dummy with sample pages and five binding styles; some of the lined pages at the end (intended for the salesman's orders) contain shorthand (with some longhand) notes about the 1893 Columbian Exposition, including "Prominent Women" and various buildings)-- Printed guide for the Art Institute of Chicago official art exhibition of a century of progress for the New World's Fair art exhibititon for 1934-- New York World's Fair 1939 jigsaw puzzle / compliments of the makers of Sloan's liniment (26 x 32 cm.)-- Envelope, with imprint: Souvenir Views of the New York World's Fair, [1934] (addressed to Wm. Hatt, Vallejo California, from J. Geraghty, with three 2 cent U.S. postage stamps featuring John Adams, with Brooklyn postmark-- 23 x 30 cm.)-- Admission ticket for adult, New York Worlds Fair 1964-1965 (6.5 x 9 cm.)-- Official souvenir map, New York World's Fair 1964/1965 / by the editors of Time-Life books ( 85 x 66 cm. folded to 24 x 13 cm. printed on 2 sides)-- Official souvenir flash card set New York World's Fair pictures, 1964-1965. (27 cards in box ; 9.5 x 15 cm.)
